'''The International Test and Evaluation Association (ITEA)''', is a [[professional body]] founded in 1980. Its primary purpose is to further the exchange of technical information in the field of test and evaluation. Membership is open to professionals, students and corporate bodies involved in the development and application of policy and techniques used to assess the [[Measure of effectiveness|effectiveness]], [[Reliability engineering|reliability]], and [[System safety|safety]] of new and existing [[Systems engineering|systems]] and [[Product (business)|products]].
